WEBVTT

00:05.386 --> 00:07.258
NOW...

00:07.258 --> 00:09.890
WHO CAN TELL ME THE STEPS
OF A PARTIAL LARYNGECTOMY?

00:09.890 --> 00:11.512
Meredith: IN GROUP SETTINGS,

00:11.512 --> 00:14.975
MEN ARE 75% MORE LIKELY
TO SPEAK UP THAN WOMEN,

00:14.975 --> 00:18.139
AND WHEN A WOMAN DOES SPEAK UP,
IT'S STATISTICALLY PROBABLE

00:18.139 --> 00:21.232
HER MALE COUNTERPARTS
WILL EITHER INTERRUPT HER

00:21.232 --> 00:23.064
OR SPEAK OVER HER.

00:23.064 --> 00:24.525
IT'S NOT BECAUSE THEY'RE RUDE.

00:24.525 --> 00:26.697
CROSS.
IT'S SCIENCE.

00:26.697 --> 00:29.110
THE FEMALE VOICE
IS SCIENTIFICALLY PROVEN

00:29.110 --> 00:31.742
TO BE MORE DIFFICULT
FOR A MALE BRAIN TO REGISTER.

00:31.742 --> 00:33.074
WHAT DOES THIS MEAN?

00:33.074 --> 00:35.456
IT MEANS IN THIS WORLD,

00:35.456 --> 00:37.998
WHERE MEN
ARE BIGGER, STRONGER, FASTER,

00:37.998 --> 00:40.291
IF YOU'RE NOT READY TO FIGHT,

00:40.291 --> 00:42.623
THE SILENCE WILL KILL YOU.

00:42.623 --> 00:43.714
[ HORNS HONKING ]
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

00:43.714 --> 00:45.256
THIS IS KILLING ME.

00:45.256 --> 00:48.219
WE HAVE NOT MOVED
IN 10 MINUTES.

00:48.219 --> 00:49.720
[ SIGHS ]
[ BEE BUZZING ]

00:49.720 --> 00:52.883
I SWEAR THAT BUMBLEBEE HAS
PASSED THIS CAR TWICE ALREADY.

00:52.883 --> 00:55.176
IT PASSED US,
IT CIRCLED THE EARTH,

00:55.176 --> 00:56.727
AND THEN CAME BACK AROUND
TO PASS US AGAIN.

00:56.727 --> 00:58.939
YEAH, BECAUSE WE LEFT LATE
BECAUSE YOU OVERSLEPT.

00:58.939 --> 01:00.771
[ LAUGHS ]
NOT FUN WHEN YOU'RE DRIVING

01:00.771 --> 01:02.443
AND SOMEONE MAKES YOU LATE.
IF YOU WANT
TO STAY UP ALL NIGHT

01:02.443 --> 01:04.105
SCREWING AROUND WITH SOME DUDE,
I DON'T CARE

01:04.105 --> 01:06.357
TILL YOU SPEND ALL MORNING
COMPLAINING ABOUT IT IN MY CAR.

01:06.357 --> 01:07.488
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

01:07.488 --> 01:08.739
[ SIREN WAILING ]
WE SHARE A WALL.

01:08.739 --> 01:10.781
SO MOVE OUT!

01:10.781 --> 01:13.244
NOBODY TOLD YOU YOU COULD CRASH
IN AMELIA'S ROOM, ANYWAY!

01:13.244 --> 01:15.075
OKAY, IT'S NOT
AMELIA'S ROOM ANYMORE.

01:15.075 --> 01:16.497
WHAT IS THAT?

01:16.497 --> 01:18.699
TWO FIRE TRUCKS?
AND THREE AMBULANCES.

01:18.699 --> 01:21.162
THAT'S GOT TO BE LIKE
A FOUR- OR FIVE-CAR PILEUP.

01:21.162 --> 01:24.375
50 BUCKS
SAYS A BIG RIG'S INVOLVED.

01:25.126 --> 01:26.297
HEY. HEY!

01:26.297 --> 01:27.508
THAT'S NOT A GOOD IDEA.

01:27.508 --> 01:28.549
LET'S GO, KAREV.

01:28.549 --> 01:32.303
SCREW IT.

01:32.303 --> 01:34.885
[ SIRENS WAILING ]

01:39.720 --> 01:42.643
[ MAN SCREAMING ]

01:42.643 --> 01:44.275
KEPS, I COULD USE
ANOTHER SET OF HANDS HERE.

01:44.275 --> 01:45.356
I'M ON IT.

01:45.356 --> 01:46.777
[ SCREAMING CONTINUES ]

01:46.777 --> 01:49.360
WE'VE BEEN PAGING YOU
FOR HALF AN HOUR.

01:49.360 --> 01:50.401
I'VE BEEN A LITTLE BUSY.

01:54.155 --> 01:56.327
WE GOT A 45-YEAR-OLD MALE
WITH A HEAD LAC,

01:56.327 --> 01:58.409
POSITIVE LOC ON THE SCENE.

01:58.409 --> 02:00.411
ALSO HAS
ABDOMINAL CONTUSION.

02:00.411 --> 02:02.953
I'D LIKE TO SAY IT'S NOT
AS BAD AS IT LOOKS, BUT...

02:02.953 --> 02:04.745
MAJOR PILEUP,
MULTIPLE WOUNDS.

02:04.745 --> 02:06.046
A BIG RIG FLIPPED.
BIGGER MESS.

02:06.046 --> 02:07.798
DO YOU THINK HE HAS
INTRA-ABDOMINAL INJURY?

02:07.798 --> 02:09.089
WELL, THERE'S ONE WAY
TO FIND OUT.

02:09.089 --> 02:10.130
ALL RIGHT,
LET'S GET HER INSIDE.

02:10.130 --> 02:11.172
I GOT THIS. GO.

02:11.172 --> 02:14.054
[ INDISTINCT CHATTER
IN DISTANCE ]

02:19.890 --> 02:23.524
A BONY DEFORMITY
IN THE TEMPORAL REGION.

02:23.524 --> 02:24.935
5 CENTIMETER HEAD LAC.

02:24.935 --> 02:26.267
ABDOMEN'S CLEAR.

02:26.267 --> 02:28.108
PALPABLE PULSES
IN ALL FOUR EXTREMITIES.

02:28.108 --> 02:30.361
WE'VE GOT
MILD PUPILLARY ASYMMETRY.

02:30.361 --> 02:31.442
WE NEED TO GET
A HEAD C.T.

02:31.442 --> 02:33.324
LET'S PAGE NEURO.
MM-HMM.

02:33.324 --> 02:35.366
STARTING TO REGRET TAKING
THAT TOUR OF THE CITY TODAY.

02:35.366 --> 02:36.987
[ GROANS ]
NO RAIN.

02:36.987 --> 02:39.079
THOUGHT
IT WAS A GOOD IDEA.

02:39.079 --> 02:40.411
I GOT
MORE THAN I BARGAINED FOR.

02:40.411 --> 02:41.742
Ben: YEAH, HEY,
DR. WARREN HERE.
[ CHUCKLES ]

02:41.742 --> 02:44.164
WELL, YOU DID HIT YOUR HEAD
PRETTY GOOD, LOU...

02:44.164 --> 02:45.206
LISTEN, WE NEED A NEURO CONSULT
DOWN IN TRAUMA ONE.
...BUT WE'RE GONNA GET YOU
FIXED UP.

02:45.206 --> 02:46.747
WASN'T MY MOST GRACEFUL
LANDING, EITHER.

02:46.747 --> 02:47.748
YEAH, SURE. I'LL HOLD.
[ CHUCKLES ]

02:47.748 --> 02:49.880
PUSHING 150 OF FENTANYL.

02:49.880 --> 02:51.171
THIS SHOULD HELP
WITH THE PAIN.

02:51.171 --> 02:53.133
YOU KNOW THEY HAD A WALL
AT PIKE'S MARKET

02:53.133 --> 02:55.756
COVERED
IN PEOPLE'S CHEWING GUM?

02:55.756 --> 02:57.758
Ben: OKAY, WELL, WHEN YOU DO,
SEND THEM DOWN, OKAY?
I DO, IN FACT, KNOW THAT, LOU.
I GREW UP HERE.

02:57.758 --> 02:59.560
MM.
THANKS.

02:59.560 --> 03:00.891
[ SIGHS ]

03:00.891 --> 03:01.932
WHERE'S NEURO?

03:01.932 --> 03:03.264
PAGED. NO RESPONSE.

03:03.264 --> 03:04.395
WELL, THEN GO GET THEM.

03:04.395 --> 03:06.227
[ SIGHS ]

03:07.768 --> 03:09.109
ANY PAIN HERE, LOU?

03:09.109 --> 03:10.481
JUST A LITTLE SORE.
A LITTLE SORE?

03:10.481 --> 03:11.612
[ GROANS ]

03:11.612 --> 03:13.193
HE'S LOST HIS PULSE!

03:13.193 --> 03:14.985
[ GROANS ]
ALL RIGHT, COVER YOUR EARS.

03:14.985 --> 03:15.816
WHY?

03:15.816 --> 03:17.117
[ BONE CRACKS ]
[ SCREAMS ]

03:17.117 --> 03:18.279
THAT'S WHY.

03:18.279 --> 03:20.321
Amelia: I WANT
HOURLY NEURO CHECKS ON BED 6,

03:20.321 --> 03:21.662
SIGN OFF
ON BEDS 4 AND 8.

03:21.662 --> 03:23.123
BED 7.
WHAT?

03:23.123 --> 03:25.376
BED 7. WE DON'T HAVE
A PATIENT IN BED 8.
RIGHT.

03:25.376 --> 03:28.208
SO BUSY IN HERE,
WHO CAN REMEMBER?
[ PAGER BUZZES ]

03:28.208 --> 03:29.420
WE'RE
BEING PAGED TO --

03:29.420 --> 03:30.461
TRAUMA 1.

03:30.461 --> 03:32.673
DR. GREY.
AND TRAUMA 3.
DR. HUNT.

03:32.673 --> 03:35.596
BOTH URGENT, NOT CRITICAL.
DO WANT HUNT FIRST OR GREY?

03:35.596 --> 03:37.888
DR. GREY TOLD ME
TO COME FIND YOU.
REALLY?

03:37.888 --> 03:39.139
MEREDITH ACTUALLY ASKED
FOR ME,

03:39.139 --> 03:41.051
OR DID SHE JUST WANT NEURO
IN GENERAL?

03:41.051 --> 03:42.263
I-I DON'T REMEMBER.

03:42.263 --> 03:43.684
[ SCOFFS ]
YEAH, YOU DO.

03:43.684 --> 03:46.847
HAVE GREY GIVE US A PAGE IF
HER PATIENT BECOMES CRITICAL.

03:46.847 --> 03:48.188
WHERE'S HUNT?
TRAUMA 3, RIGHT?

03:48.188 --> 03:49.940
3. [ SIGHS ]

03:49.940 --> 03:51.652
WE'LL BE THERE
IN LESS THAN 10 MINUTES.

03:51.652 --> 03:53.484
Andrew: DR. WARREN,
SOME HELP OVER HERE, PLEASE.

03:53.484 --> 03:54.485
COMING THROUGH!

03:54.485 --> 03:56.116
[ GASPING ]

03:56.116 --> 03:58.198
Man: I NEED O2 TANKS OVER HERE
FOR TRANSPORT.

03:58.198 --> 04:00.321
WE'RE OUT HERE
VISITING MY SISTER.

04:00.321 --> 04:03.163
SHE AND MY KIDS
ARE ON A GIRLS' DAY OUT.

04:03.163 --> 04:05.326
SO I DECIDED
TO GO SEE THE SPACE NEEDLE.

04:05.326 --> 04:07.037
NOW I'M SEEING
ALL KINDS OF NEEDLES.

04:07.037 --> 04:09.870
[ LAUGHS ]

04:09.870 --> 04:11.752
YEAH, IT'S CORNY.
I KNOW.

04:11.752 --> 04:13.374
SORRY.

04:13.374 --> 04:15.586
MY DAUGHTERS TELL ME
I MAKE THE WORST JOKES.

04:15.586 --> 04:17.878
HOW MANY KIDS
DO YOU HAVE?

04:17.878 --> 04:19.340
TWO.

04:19.340 --> 04:21.592
THEY'RE 10 AND 6.
AWW. SWEET.

04:21.592 --> 04:24.385
AND THEY ARE SMART, MAN.
[ CHUCKLES ]

04:24.385 --> 04:26.387
THEY'RE SMARTER THAN I...

04:28.058 --> 04:29.390
WHOA!
OKAY.

04:29.390 --> 04:30.731
WHAT ARE WE LOOKING AT?

04:30.731 --> 04:32.693
UM...
COME ON, SPEAK UP!

04:32.693 --> 04:34.485
A TONIC CLONIC SEIZURE.

04:34.485 --> 04:35.486
THAT'S RIGHT.
LET'S ROLL HIM.

04:35.486 --> 04:37.157
1, 2, 3.

04:37.157 --> 04:38.989
OKAY, WHAT DO WE DO NOW?

04:38.989 --> 04:39.990
WE WAIT FOR IT TO PASS.

04:39.990 --> 04:42.953
WE WAIT FOR IT TO PASS.

04:42.953 --> 04:44.995
IT'S GOING ON TOO LONG.

04:44.995 --> 04:46.457
WE NEED 10 OF LORAZEPAM.
IT'S LOCKED IN PHARMA.

04:46.457 --> 04:47.247
GO -- NOW.

04:48.869 --> 04:50.831
IT'S OKAY, LOU.
I GOT YOU.

04:55.756 --> 04:57.087
[ EXHALES SLOWLY ]

04:57.087 --> 04:58.759
OOH.

04:58.759 --> 05:00.921
THAT WAS A BIG ONE.

05:00.921 --> 05:03.013
OKAY.

05:06.266 --> 05:08.429
OKAY.

05:08.429 --> 05:10.020
OKAY.

05:13.434 --> 05:14.895
ALL RIGHT.

05:14.895 --> 05:17.528
OH. HE'S GONNA NEED
A NEW GOWN AND FRESH SHEETS.

05:17.528 --> 05:19.109
OH, I HATE IT
WHEN THEY DO THAT.

05:19.109 --> 05:21.442
COULD YOU GET AN ORDERLY?
DO YOU MIND?

05:28.999 --> 05:31.001
BE RIGHT BACK.

05:31.001 --> 05:32.713
OKAY,
HEY, THERE'S NO RUSH,

05:32.713 --> 05:34.915
BUT IF YOU DO SEE NEURO,
GET THEM UP HERE, PLEASE.
MM-HMM.

05:37.588 --> 05:38.759
OKAY, LOU.

06:16.997 --> 06:18.959
[ SIREN WAILING IN DISTANCE ]

06:54.535 --> 06:55.666
LOU.

06:55.666 --> 06:58.589
[ MUMBLING ]
LOU.

06:58.589 --> 07:00.420
YOU NEED TO LAY DOWN.

07:00.420 --> 07:01.672
YOU SHOULDN'T BE UP.

07:01.672 --> 07:03.383
LOU.
[ MOANING ]

07:03.383 --> 07:04.675
LET'S GET BACK ON THE BED,
LOU.

07:04.675 --> 07:06.967
[ GRUNTS ]
MM!

07:06.967 --> 07:08.388
[ GRUNTS ]

07:08.388 --> 07:09.389
[ GRUNTS ]

07:09.389 --> 07:11.391
UGH! AAH!

07:13.854 --> 07:15.856
[ BOTH GRUNTING ]

07:16.557 --> 07:18.358
COMING THROUGH!

07:18.358 --> 07:21.652
Woman:
I NEED THAT CHEST X-RAY!

07:21.652 --> 07:23.904
V-FIB, CHARGE TO 300.

07:23.904 --> 07:25.275
CHARGED.

07:25.275 --> 07:27.568
ALL RIGHT.
ALL RIGHT, READY?

07:27.568 --> 07:29.449
CLEAR!
[ BEEPING ]

07:29.449 --> 07:31.532
COME ON.

07:31.532 --> 07:33.333
COME ON,
COME ON, COME ON.

07:33.333 --> 07:35.415
[ FLATLINE ]
[ SIGHS ] RIGHT.
CLEAR!

07:35.415 --> 07:37.207
[ BEEPING ]

07:37.207 --> 07:39.079
[ THUD ]
COME ON.

07:39.079 --> 07:40.921
[ FLATLINE CONTINUES ]

07:44.384 --> 07:45.716
[ SIGHS ] OKAY.

07:45.716 --> 07:47.508
I'M CALLING IT.

07:47.508 --> 07:51.011
TIME OF DEATH -- 11:42.

07:52.803 --> 07:55.095
CRAP.

07:55.095 --> 07:57.187
I REALLY THOUGHT
WE HAD HIM.

07:57.187 --> 07:59.940
YEAH, ME TOO.

07:59.940 --> 08:01.942
[ SIGHS ]

08:34.975 --> 08:38.188
[ WHIMPERING ]

08:59.079 --> 09:01.501
I NEED SOME HELP IN HERE NOW!

09:04.124 --> 09:05.716
TRAUMA PANEL.
SEND BLOOD FOR A CROSSMATCH.

09:05.716 --> 09:07.087
BELLY IS SOFT.

09:07.087 --> 09:08.258
April:
BRUISING ON THE LEFT CHEST.

09:08.258 --> 09:09.590
DECREASED BREATH SOUNDS
ON THE LEFT.

09:09.590 --> 09:10.761
ART LINE IS GOING IN.

09:10.761 --> 09:13.473
PULSE OX IS DOWN TO 88.

09:13.473 --> 09:15.095
Richard: FOR A TRAUMA SERIES.
HOOK UP THOSE MONITORS.

09:15.095 --> 09:16.386
WE NEED AN WIDE BORE I.V.

09:16.386 --> 09:19.810
GET ORTHO HERE.
ADD SOME LEFT ARM AND LEG FILMS.

09:19.810 --> 09:21.812
HAS ANYONE TOLD THE CHIEF?
OKAY, DO NOT PAGE HER.

09:21.812 --> 09:23.944
THIS IS ONE PATIENT.
WE CAN DO THIS ONE, OKAY?

09:23.944 --> 09:25.485
SHE HAS TO HANDLE
EVERYTHING ELSE.

09:25.485 --> 09:27.608
THE GUY WHO DID THIS --
HE WAS STABLE, NON-AGGRESSIVE.

09:27.608 --> 09:29.189
HE WASN'T A THREAT.

09:29.189 --> 09:31.451
I LEFT FOR LIKE FIVE MINUTES,
AND THIS HAPPENS.

09:31.451 --> 09:32.743
HE WAS POSTICTAL.

09:32.743 --> 09:34.244
HYPER-AGGRESSION
CAN OCCUR AFTER A SEIZURE.

09:34.244 --> 09:35.616
TEMPORARY FUGUE STATE.

09:35.616 --> 09:37.537
HE WON'T EVEN REMEMBER IT.
WHERE IS HE NOW?

09:37.537 --> 09:39.660
RESTRAINED, AND BEING TREATED
RIGHT NEXT DOOR.

09:39.660 --> 09:40.961
[ DOOR OPENS ]

09:41.872 --> 09:43.253
[ SIGHS ]

09:43.253 --> 09:45.335
HER VEIN'S COLLAPSED.
I CAN'T GET IN.

09:45.335 --> 09:46.877
Owen:
PUT IN A CENTRAL LINE.

09:46.877 --> 09:49.339
I GOT IT.
OH, OKAY.

09:49.339 --> 09:52.973
Richard: OBVIOUS DISLOCATION
OF THE LEFT ELBOW.

09:52.973 --> 09:55.515
WE GOT
SOME LEFT KNEE SWELLING.

09:55.515 --> 09:57.888
April: RIB FRACTURES ON THE LEFT
WITH PALPABLE CREPITUS.

09:57.888 --> 10:00.100
GET ORTHO HERE.
GET A BLOOD GAS
FROM THE ART LINE.

10:00.100 --> 10:01.982
Owen:
WE NEED A WIDE BORE I.V.
NO OBVIOUS FLAIL.

10:04.685 --> 10:05.896
[ HEART BEATING ]

10:05.896 --> 10:09.109
[ NO AUDIO ]

10:11.401 --> 10:12.572
DAMN IT.
SEND FOR A TRAUMA PANEL
AND A CROSS.

10:12.572 --> 10:14.324
SOMEBODY GET JACKSON IN HERE
RIGHT NOW!

10:14.324 --> 10:17.287
ON IT.
GREY. GREY, WE'RE GONNA SHOOT
A QUICK X-RAY, ALL RIGHT?

10:17.287 --> 10:18.408
HI. I'M HERE.

10:19.539 --> 10:22.242
[ NO AUDIO ]

10:36.346 --> 10:38.138
Richard: 1, 2, 3, EASY.

10:38.138 --> 10:40.060
[ SCREAMS ]
EASY.
EASY, EASY, EASY, EASY.

10:40.060 --> 10:41.261
OKAY. EASY.

10:41.261 --> 10:43.603
ALL RIGHT, OKAY.
ALL RIGHT, EVERYBODY BACK.

10:43.603 --> 10:45.265
[ GROANS ]
OKAY.

10:45.265 --> 10:46.316
ALL RIGHT, READY?
ON THREE.

10:46.316 --> 10:48.358
1, 2, 3.

10:48.358 --> 10:49.359
[ SCREAMS ]

10:49.359 --> 10:50.731
ALL RIGHT, EASY.

10:50.731 --> 10:52.482
-NO, NO, NO, NO.
-MEREDITH, IT'S OKAY.

10:52.482 --> 10:54.695
IT'S OKAY, IT'S OKAY.
IT'S OKAY.

10:54.695 --> 10:55.986
IT'S OKAY.

10:55.986 --> 10:57.948
WE'RE HERE.
WHAT HAVE WE --

10:57.948 --> 11:00.330
POSSIBLE CONCUSSION,
HEAD CONTUSIONS,

11:00.330 --> 11:02.372
MULTIPLE BLUNT-FORCE BLOWS
TO THE HEAD AND NECK.

11:02.372 --> 11:04.084
IT'S -- IT'S GREY.
I'M SORRY.

11:04.084 --> 11:05.545
I THOUGHT YOU KNEW.

11:05.545 --> 11:06.787
DR. SHEPHERD?

11:06.787 --> 11:08.789
[ MONITOR BEEPING RAPIDLY ]

11:08.789 --> 11:10.630
DR. SHEPHERD.

11:10.630 --> 11:12.002
DR. SHEPHERD!

11:13.794 --> 11:16.176
HERE'S THE FILMS.
OKAY.
PRESSURE'S 90 OVER 60.

11:16.176 --> 11:17.597
Maggie:
SHE'S GOT A 30% PNEUMO.

11:17.597 --> 11:18.969
NO OBVIOUS EFFUSION.
SHE NEEDS A CHEST TUBE.

11:18.969 --> 11:20.350
I NEED A 36 TUBE,
BETADINE,

11:20.350 --> 11:22.432
AND 6 1/2 GLOVES.
Alex: SET UP THE PLEUROVAC.

11:22.432 --> 11:24.064
[ HEART BEATING ]

11:28.688 --> 11:30.400
JUST GOT LABS.
CRIT IS STABLE.

11:30.400 --> 11:32.152
OH, GOOD.
DRAW BLOOD GAS FROM THE A-LINE.

11:32.813 --> 11:33.904
WHAT IS THIS?
WHAT THE HELL HAPPENED?

11:33.904 --> 11:35.075
Richard: SHE WAS ATTACKED
BY A PATIENT.

11:35.075 --> 11:36.196
Owen: THE NECK
IS BRUISED AND SWOLLEN.

11:36.196 --> 11:37.657
SHE NEEDS
AN AIRWAY EVALUATION.

11:37.657 --> 11:38.949
ALL RIGHT,
I'M ON IT, I'M ON IT.

11:38.949 --> 11:41.281
Stephanie: NO BONY DEFORMITY.
POSITIVE BATTLE'S SIGN.

11:41.281 --> 11:43.453
OKAY, MEREDITH, WE'RE
GONNA HAVE TO PUT IN A
CHEST TUBE, ALL RIGHT?

11:43.453 --> 11:44.244
YOUR LUNG IS COLLAPSING.

11:45.035 --> 11:46.917
[ NO AUDIO ]

11:49.249 --> 11:51.331
AND THIS IS GONNA BURN.
I'M INJECTING THE LIDO.

11:51.331 --> 11:52.632
YOU CAN'T WORK
ON YOUR FAMILY.

11:52.632 --> 11:54.424
EVERYBODY IN THIS DAMN ROOM
IS HER FAMILY.

11:54.424 --> 11:56.426
IT'S FINE.
HERE WE GO.

11:56.426 --> 11:57.217
[ MEREDITH GROANS ]

12:01.431 --> 12:03.263
[ GASPS, COUGHS ]

12:03.263 --> 12:05.305
BREATHE, MER, BREATHE.
BREATHE, BREATHE.
Maggie: CHEST TUBE IS IN.

12:05.305 --> 12:07.517
[ GROANS ]
OKAY, EASY, EASY, EASY.
EASY, EASY.

12:07.517 --> 12:09.399
PULSE OX IS COMING BACK UP.
88, 90.

12:13.523 --> 12:15.776
NO EVIDENCE
OF TRAUMATIC BRAIN INJURY.

12:15.776 --> 12:17.407
NO -- NO --
NO FOCAL DEFICITS.

12:17.407 --> 12:19.449
UH, EXCEPT --

12:19.449 --> 12:22.162
UH, UH, DR. GREY, I NEED YOU
TO MOVE YOUR FINGERS FOR ME.

12:23.784 --> 12:26.036
OR YOUR TOES.

12:29.329 --> 12:31.922
COME ON. JUST COME ON.
WIGGLE SOMETHING.

12:31.922 --> 12:33.333
Alex: SHE RESPONDED
TO THE PAINFUL STIMULUS.

12:33.333 --> 12:35.215
IT DOESN'T MAKE SENSE...
PULSE OX IS DROPPING AGAIN.

12:35.215 --> 12:37.587
[ WHEEZING ]
...UNLESS...

12:37.587 --> 12:39.139
THE CHEST TUBE
HAS A SMALL AIR LEAK.

12:39.139 --> 12:41.051
NO, SHE HAS
MILD SUB-Q EMPHYSEMA.

12:41.051 --> 12:42.722
WE NEED TO SECURE THIS AIRWAY
AND TUBE HER.

12:42.722 --> 12:44.144
GOT IT.
GUYS.

12:44.144 --> 12:45.765
GUYS.
I DON'T THINK SHE CAN HEAR US.

12:45.765 --> 12:46.766
-WHAT?
-WHAT?

12:46.766 --> 12:47.557
-ARE YOU SURE?
-NO.

12:47.557 --> 12:48.348
MER.

12:54.444 --> 12:57.157
I SEE EVIDENCE OF BAROTRAUMA,
POSSIBLY FROM THE BLOWS.

12:57.157 --> 12:58.488
I THINK
KAREV MIGHT BE RIGHT.

12:58.488 --> 12:59.860
I DON'T THINK SHE CAN HEAR
ANYTHING WE'RE SAYING.

12:59.860 --> 13:01.902
[ GASPS ]

13:01.902 --> 13:03.073
HER JAW IS LOCKED.

13:03.073 --> 13:04.164
SUCTION!
-SUCTION.

13:04.164 --> 13:05.785
CAN WE TAKE A LOOK?

13:05.785 --> 13:07.117
ALL RIGHT.
LET ME SEE.

13:07.117 --> 13:08.618
YEAH, YEAH, EASY, EASY.

13:08.618 --> 13:10.460
YEAH, WE'VE GOT A DISLOCATION
HERE, POSSIBLE FRACTURE.

13:10.460 --> 13:12.082
THERE'S NO WAY
WE'RE GETTING A TUBE IN THERE.

13:12.082 --> 13:14.714
YOU HAVE TO GET A TUBE IN.
YOU HAVE TO PRESERVE HER AIRWAY.

13:14.714 --> 13:16.006
OR WE HAVE TO TRACH HER.

13:16.006 --> 13:18.128
NO, NO, NO. UM...
ALL RIGHT, WAIT A SECOND.

13:18.128 --> 13:19.719
IF I CAN REDUCE
THE DISLOCATION,

13:19.719 --> 13:21.801
WE CAN PROBABLY GET HER MOUTH
OPEN JUST ENOUGH TO INTUBATE.

13:21.801 --> 13:23.884
IT'S GONNA HURT LIKE HELL,
THOUGH.

13:23.884 --> 13:25.015
OKAY. HANG TIGHT.

13:25.015 --> 13:27.517
I'M SORRY. HERE.
OKAY, MER.

13:27.517 --> 13:30.230
OKAY, WE'RE GONNA HAVE
TO POP YOUR JAW OPEN, OKAY?

13:30.230 --> 13:32.022
I'M SORRY. I KNOW.
BUT WE HAVE TO DO IT.

13:32.022 --> 13:33.603
AND WE'RE GONNA DO THIS
ON THE COUNT OF THREE, YOU GUYS.

13:33.603 --> 13:36.236
READY? 1...2...

13:36.987 --> 13:37.737
AAH!

13:56.296 --> 13:57.757
[ NO AUDIO ]

14:35.625 --> 14:37.587
[ NO AUDIO ]

14:57.687 --> 15:01.021
♪♪

15:03.613 --> 15:05.445
[ NO AUDIO ]

16:11.641 --> 16:13.643
[ NO AUDIO ]

17:56.035 --> 17:58.658
[ NO AUDIO ]

18:41.000 --> 18:42.912
♪♪

20:16.256 --> 20:17.547
[ NO AUDIO ]

20:29.559 --> 20:31.771
HEY.

20:31.771 --> 20:33.192
WHAT'S WRONG, MEREDITH?

20:45.915 --> 20:47.327
HEY.

21:09.389 --> 21:11.150
JUST GET IT OUT,
GET IT ALL OUT.

21:11.150 --> 21:12.602
[ CRYING ]

21:12.602 --> 21:14.103
THE TEARS, ALL THE...

21:17.897 --> 21:21.661
GOD, YOU'VE GOT
A LOT OF SNOT.

21:21.661 --> 21:22.702
[ LAUGHS ]

21:22.702 --> 21:24.364
I'M SERIOUS.
I'M FOR REAL.

21:24.364 --> 21:26.906
I MEAN, YOU MIGHT HAVE
A SERIOUS CONDITION.

21:26.906 --> 21:29.409
[ SNIFFLES ]
COME ON, WOMAN.

21:29.409 --> 21:32.672
BLOW YOUR DAMN NOSE.
[ LAUGHS ]

21:32.672 --> 21:34.334
HANG ON.

21:34.334 --> 21:35.505
MER.

21:35.505 --> 21:37.296
[ SNAPPING FINGERS ]

21:37.296 --> 21:39.218
CAN YOU HEAR ME?

21:39.218 --> 21:40.219
MM-HMM.

21:40.219 --> 21:41.220
YOU CAN HEAR ME?

21:41.220 --> 21:42.221
MM-HMM.

21:42.221 --> 21:43.683
[ CHUCKLES ]
YOU CAN HEAR ME?

21:43.683 --> 21:44.804
MM-HMM.
[ LAUGHS ]

21:44.804 --> 21:46.976
[ Laughing ] OH, MY GOD.

21:46.976 --> 21:49.188
OH.

21:49.188 --> 21:51.351
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

22:01.441 --> 22:03.032
Jackson: IT IS IMPORTANT
THAT YOU CONTINUE THE
VOICE REST, OKAY?

22:03.032 --> 22:04.364
YOUR TRACHEAL INJURY
IS NOT...

22:04.364 --> 22:05.705
[Loudly] FULLY HEALED,

22:05.705 --> 22:06.826
AND YOUR LATEST AUDIOMETRY

22:06.826 --> 22:08.998
SHOWS THAT THE HEARING
IN YOUR RIGHT EAR

22:08.998 --> 22:11.411
HAS ALMOST
COMPLETELY RETURNED.

22:11.411 --> 22:14.794
ON YOUR LEFT, YOU'RE LOOKING
AT ABOUT 55%, WHICH IS GOOD.

22:14.794 --> 22:15.875
IT'S ONLY BEEN A FEW WEEKS,
YOU KNOW,

22:15.875 --> 22:17.377
SO I'M NOT CONCERNED
ABOUT IT.

22:17.377 --> 22:20.420
IT'S GONNA COME BACK, MEREDITH,
OKAY?

22:20.420 --> 22:21.591
[ Loudly ]
I WANT YOU TO CONTINUE TO --

22:21.591 --> 22:22.802
MM.

22:22.802 --> 22:24.223
[ Softly ]
I-I WANT YOU TO CONTINUE

22:24.223 --> 22:26.055
TO MOVE YOUR FINGERS
WHILE IN THE CAST,

22:26.055 --> 22:28.468
AND YOU WILL REMAIN
NON-WEIGHT-BEARING ON YOUR LEG

22:28.468 --> 22:30.059
UNTIL WE TAKE THE CAST OFF.

22:30.059 --> 22:32.892
YEAH, THERE'S A LITTLE SWELLING
IN THAT LEFT LEG.

22:32.892 --> 22:35.274
IT'S PROBABLY LOCAL EDEMA,

22:35.274 --> 22:37.567
BUT I'VE ORDERED A DOPPLER
JUST TO BE SAFE.

22:37.567 --> 22:38.608
ANYTHING ELSE?

22:38.608 --> 22:39.899
-MNH-MNH.
-NO.

22:47.657 --> 22:49.118
Jackson: LOU?
WHAT'S -- WHO'S LOU?

22:49.118 --> 22:51.250
THE PATIENT
WHO ATTACKED MEREDITH.

22:51.250 --> 22:52.622
I'VE BEEN CALLING HIM
SOMETHING ELSE.

22:52.622 --> 22:55.545
LOOK, WE DON'T HAVE
TO GO INTO THAT RIGHT NOW.

22:57.957 --> 22:59.298
SHE WANTS TO KNOW.
TELL HER.

22:59.298 --> 23:01.761
OKAY.

23:01.761 --> 23:05.425
LOU SUFFERED A SEVERE EPIDURAL
HEMATOMA IN THE ACCIDENT.

23:05.425 --> 23:07.006
IT'S WHAT CAUSED
THE SEIZURE.

23:07.006 --> 23:11.511
WE THINK HE WAS IN A POSTICTAL
STATE WHEN HE ATTACKED.

23:11.511 --> 23:13.433
AFTER A FEW MINUTES,

23:13.433 --> 23:16.436
HE WOKE UP AND HAD NO IDEA
WHAT HE HAD DONE.

23:16.436 --> 23:19.318
HE HAD SURGERY
AND WAS DISCHARGED.

23:19.318 --> 23:22.982
HE'S DOING FINE.
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

23:24.233 --> 23:26.446
LOU HAS REACHED OUT.

23:26.446 --> 23:29.408
HE HAS MADE A COUPLE
OF REQUESTS TO SEE YOU.

23:29.408 --> 23:30.910
MNH-MNH.
I THINK...

23:30.910 --> 23:32.952
...HE WOULD JUST LIKE
TO APOLOGIZE.

23:32.952 --> 23:35.084
Alex: IT'S OKAY.

23:35.084 --> 23:37.667
SHE'S KICKING US OUT.

23:37.667 --> 23:38.538
Meredith: MM, MM.
LET'S GO.

23:40.460 --> 23:42.802
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
GO AHEAD.

23:42.802 --> 23:44.303
[ WHITEBOARD SQUEAKING ]

23:44.303 --> 23:46.425
Callie: APOLOGIZE?
ARE YOU SERIOUS?

23:46.425 --> 23:47.807
Bailey:
OF COURSE I'M SERIOUS.

23:47.807 --> 23:49.218
Maggie:
YEAH, I DON'T SEE WHY.

23:49.218 --> 23:50.550
BECAUSE THE LAST TIME
THAT WOMAN

23:50.550 --> 23:51.931
GOT HURT
WORKING FOR THIS HOSPITAL,

23:51.931 --> 23:53.432
SHE PURCHASED
THIS HOSPITAL.

23:53.432 --> 23:54.934
THAT IS WHY.

23:54.934 --> 23:57.396
AND WHAT DO YOU THINK WILL
HAPPEN IF SHE SEES HIM AGAIN?

23:57.396 --> 23:58.437
Jackson: NOTHING GOOD.

23:58.437 --> 23:59.689
EXACTLY.

23:59.689 --> 24:02.271
[ THUNDER CRASHES ]

24:43.232 --> 24:45.024
[ THUNDER RUMBLES ]

24:50.660 --> 24:53.162
GOOD, GOOD.

24:56.115 --> 24:58.708
ALL RIGHT.
TRY AND LIFT YOUR LEG FOR ME.

24:58.708 --> 25:00.960
GOOD, GOOD.
DECENT MOBILITY.

25:06.756 --> 25:08.217
I DON'T KNOW.

25:08.217 --> 25:11.130
WELL, WE'RE DONE,
AND IT'S ALL GOOD, SO...

25:11.130 --> 25:12.221
THANKS.

25:12.221 --> 25:14.764
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

25:14.764 --> 25:18.688
UH, HE HAS BEEN WORKING
A LOT OF NIGHT SHIFTS,

25:18.688 --> 25:20.189
AND SHE'S BEEN...

25:20.189 --> 25:23.643
THEY HAVEN'T BEEN TALKING,
I DON'T THINK,

25:23.643 --> 25:26.525
OR HANGING OR ANYTHING,
FROM WHAT I CAN TELL.

25:26.525 --> 25:28.988
SO, ANYWAY...

25:28.988 --> 25:30.740
LET'S DO THIS AGAIN.
[ SIGHS ]

25:30.740 --> 25:32.912
FOLLOW THE PEN.

25:32.912 --> 25:34.533
[ LAUGHS ]

25:36.656 --> 25:39.498
OKAY, THIS ISN'T
EXACTLY THE RIGHT SHADE,

25:39.498 --> 25:42.331
BUT IT'S DOING A PRETTY GOOD JOB
OF COVERING THE BRUISING.

25:42.331 --> 25:44.293
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]
ALL RIGHT.

25:44.293 --> 25:46.255
SO...

25:46.255 --> 25:48.257
DON'T TRY AND GET UP,
OKAY?

25:48.257 --> 25:50.429
JUST LET THEM COME TO YOU.

25:50.429 --> 25:51.881
AND SMILE.

25:51.881 --> 25:54.513
BUT TRY NOT
TO OPEN YOUR MOUTH

25:54.513 --> 25:56.225
BECAUSE IT'S STILL
PRETTY SWOLLEN IN THERE

25:56.225 --> 25:59.268
AND THE WIRES --
THE METAL WIRES --

25:59.268 --> 26:00.890
THEY'RE A LITTLE SCARY.

26:03.482 --> 26:05.524
YOU READY?

26:05.524 --> 26:06.946
OKAY, ALL RIGHT.

26:13.492 --> 26:15.955
HEY, HEY, HEY!
LOOK WHO'S HERE, GUYS!

26:15.955 --> 26:17.747
YOUR MOMMY IS SO EXCITED
TO SEE YOU!

26:17.747 --> 26:19.078
COME HERE.

26:19.078 --> 26:20.870
Alex: COME ON IN.
GO AHEAD. GO TELL HER.

26:20.870 --> 26:21.751
TELL HER
WHAT WE TALKED ABOUT, OKAY?

26:21.751 --> 26:23.042
I DON'T WANT TO.

26:23.042 --> 26:24.543
OH, COME ON, ZOLA.

26:24.543 --> 26:27.006
YOU ASK ME EVERY DAY,
"WHEN CAN WE GO SEE MOMMY?"

26:27.006 --> 26:28.758
LOOK.
SHE'S RIGHT OVER THERE.

26:28.758 --> 26:29.919
GO GIVE HER A BIG HUG!

26:29.919 --> 26:31.260
NO!

26:31.260 --> 26:33.713
NO, NO, NO!

26:33.713 --> 26:35.474
[ Muffled ]
ZO-ZO, COME SEE MOMMY.

26:35.474 --> 26:37.556
I WANT TO GO.

26:37.556 --> 26:38.888
ALEX: Come on.

26:38.888 --> 26:40.720
[ SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY ]

26:40.720 --> 26:42.481
[ Muffled ]
ZO-ZO, COME SEE MOMMY, HONEY.

26:42.481 --> 26:43.482
COME ON!

26:43.482 --> 26:44.894
ZO-ZO!
[ ELLIS CRYING ]

26:44.894 --> 26:46.565
COME SEE MOMMY, HONEY!

26:46.565 --> 26:47.857
COME ON, HONEY!

26:47.857 --> 26:49.568
COME ON, ZO!

26:49.568 --> 26:50.820
[ CRYING CONTINUES ]

26:50.820 --> 26:52.652
COME ON, HONEY.
PLEASE.

26:52.652 --> 26:53.903
ZOLA, COME ON.
YOU KNOW --
YOU KNOW WHAT?

26:53.903 --> 26:55.825
LET'S JUST, UM --
LET'S DO THIS LATER.

26:55.825 --> 26:57.076
NO.
LET'S DO THIS LATER.
IT'S NOT --

26:57.076 --> 26:58.698
NO, NO, NO!
IT'S NOT OKAY.

26:58.698 --> 26:59.999
[ SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY ]

26:59.999 --> 27:01.741
COME ON, COME ON,
COME ON, COME ON.

27:01.741 --> 27:03.372
COME ON, COME ON.
LET'S DO THIS LATER.

27:03.372 --> 27:05.955
LET'S DO THIS LATER.
WE'RE GONNA DO IT LATER, OKAY?

27:05.955 --> 27:07.416
WE'RE GONNA DO IT LATER.
OKAY.

27:07.416 --> 27:08.798
[ CRYING CONTINUES ]

27:08.798 --> 27:11.380
OKAY, DOES ANYBODY WANT ANYTHING
YUMMY FROM THE CAFETERIA?

27:11.380 --> 27:14.383
ALL RIGHT.

27:14.383 --> 27:16.345
ZOLA!

27:17.887 --> 27:19.889
[ CRYING ]

27:22.892 --> 27:25.394
[ GROANS ]

27:25.394 --> 27:26.435
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

27:26.435 --> 27:27.727
DR. ROBBINS WANTED --

27:27.727 --> 27:29.398
[ Muffled ]
COME IN HERE!
DR. GREY.

27:29.398 --> 27:30.529
GET IN HERE!
DR. GREY.

27:30.529 --> 27:31.981
OKAY, OKAY.

27:31.981 --> 27:32.822
OKAY.
I CAN'T BREATHE!

27:32.822 --> 27:33.903
OKAY, YOU'RE OKAY.

27:33.903 --> 27:34.984
HANG ON, HANG ON.

27:34.984 --> 27:36.575
DEEP BREATH.
DEEP BREATH.

27:36.575 --> 27:37.907
I NEED YOU
TO BREATHE FOR ME.

27:37.907 --> 27:39.198
[ GROANING ]
BREATHE FOR ME, DR. GREY.

27:39.198 --> 27:40.449
BREATHE.

27:40.449 --> 27:41.871
[ WHIMPERING ]

27:41.871 --> 27:43.372
STAY STILL.
[ COUGHS ]

27:43.372 --> 27:46.165
STAY STILL.
I'M GONNA GET YOU SOME AIR.

27:46.165 --> 27:48.457
JUST STAY STILL.
I'M GONNA OPEN YOU UP, OKAY?

27:48.457 --> 27:50.669
OKAY.
I'M OPENING YOU UP.

27:50.669 --> 27:52.591
STAY STILL. PLEASE.

27:52.591 --> 27:54.053
[ GROANING ]
OKAY.

27:54.053 --> 27:55.344
PLEASE.

27:55.344 --> 27:56.846
[ GROANING ]

27:56.846 --> 27:59.008
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

27:59.008 --> 28:00.259
PLEASE.

28:00.259 --> 28:02.561
OKAY.

28:02.561 --> 28:04.513
HOLD ON.

28:04.513 --> 28:06.726
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

28:06.726 --> 28:08.187
ALL RIGHT.
GOOD.

28:08.187 --> 28:10.399
HEY, WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU DOING?!

28:10.399 --> 28:12.772
Penny: SHE -- SHE WAS
HAVING A PANIC ATTACK.
SHE COULDN'T BREATHE.

28:12.772 --> 28:14.944
DO YOU NOT REALIZE HOW DELICATE
THE JAW ACTUALLY IS?
DR. AVERY, SHE --

28:14.944 --> 28:16.816
YOU COULD JEOPARDIZE
THE ENTIRE HEALING PROCESS HERE.

28:16.816 --> 28:19.078
SHE COULDN'T BREATHE!
LOOK AT HER!

28:19.078 --> 28:21.530
SHE'S BEEN STUCK IN THIS ROOM
IN THAT BED FOR WEEKS.

28:21.530 --> 28:23.122
SHE CAN'T MOVE.
SHE CAN'T TALK.

28:23.122 --> 28:25.124
BUT I'M HER SURGEON NOW,
RIGHT?

28:25.124 --> 28:26.876
YOU CAN'T COME IN HERE
AND JUST TAKE OUT HER WIRES.

28:26.876 --> 28:28.587
SHE IS MY PATIENT.

28:28.587 --> 28:31.040
I KNOW WHAT I AM DOING!

28:31.040 --> 28:33.172
YOU CAN REWIRE HER JAW
TOMORROW MORNING,

28:33.172 --> 28:34.754
BUT RIGHT NOW,
SHE NEEDED SOME AIR,

28:34.754 --> 28:36.465
SO I GOT HER
SOME DAMN AIR!

28:36.465 --> 28:40.469
[ PANTING ]

28:40.469 --> 28:42.051
♪♪

28:50.189 --> 28:51.400
I BROUGHT YOU SOMETHING
TO EAT -- DRINK.

28:51.400 --> 28:53.652
MM.
I KNOW. I'M SORRY.

28:53.652 --> 28:56.445
MORNING!

28:56.445 --> 28:57.486
OH, COME ON.

28:57.486 --> 28:59.158
OR NOT.

28:59.949 --> 29:01.620
[ CUP THUDS ]
HOW'S THE PAIN TODAY?

29:02.701 --> 29:03.702
[ THUDS ]

29:03.702 --> 29:05.124
AND THE DISCOMFORT?

29:05.124 --> 29:06.125
[ THUDS LOUDLY ]

29:06.125 --> 29:07.286
WELL, HER ENERGY'S UP.

29:07.286 --> 29:08.828
ALL RIGHT. I'M SORRY.

29:08.828 --> 29:10.749
I HAVE ALL OF FIVE MINUTES
TO UPDATE YOU ON THE MIRACLE...

29:10.749 --> 29:13.292
THAT I'VE BEEN WORKING
ON YOUR SERVICE THIS WEEK,

29:13.292 --> 29:15.714
BUT IT SEEMS LIKE A BAD TIME.

29:15.714 --> 29:18.637
UH, I'M GONNA CHECK IN
AND UPDATE YOU LATER.

29:18.637 --> 29:22.761
MAYBE WE ALL
COULD CHECK IN LATER.

29:23.762 --> 29:24.804
YEAH.

29:27.016 --> 29:29.979
I'M JUST GONNA...

29:29.979 --> 29:31.310
LEAVE THAT.

29:40.699 --> 29:42.201
[ THUDDING ]

29:47.957 --> 29:50.579
Woman: WHOA.
WHAT HAPPENED?

29:50.579 --> 29:52.081
EVERYTHING OKAY?

29:53.833 --> 29:56.795
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]
Woman: NURSES STATION.

29:56.795 --> 29:58.337
YEAH, OKAY.
I GOT IT.

29:58.337 --> 29:59.508
YOU DON'T WANT
TO LOOK AT ME.

29:59.508 --> 30:01.720
I GET IT.
[ CHUCKLES ]

30:03.182 --> 30:06.095
DO YOU THINK
THAT I WANT TO BE OUT THERE

30:06.095 --> 30:07.476
HANGING OUT
OUTSIDE YOUR DOOR

30:07.476 --> 30:09.098
LIKE SOME PATHETIC LITTLE RAT
LOOKING FOR SCRAPS?

30:09.098 --> 30:11.480
DO YOU THINK
THAT FEELS GOOD FOR ME?

30:11.480 --> 30:13.692
I-I HAVE BEEN OUT THERE

30:13.692 --> 30:16.025
TRYING TO FIGURE OUT
HOW TO MAKE AMENDS...

30:16.025 --> 30:17.857
AS IF THAT WOULD MATTER
TO YOU.

30:28.287 --> 30:30.329
I KNOW I'M A MESS...

30:30.329 --> 30:32.872
WHO TALKS TOO MUCH
AND FEELS TOO MUCH,

30:32.872 --> 30:34.373
AND I KNOW
THAT IT DRIVES YOU CRAZY,

30:34.373 --> 30:37.796
BUT THAT IS THE ONE WAY
I KNOW HOW TO STAY SOBER,

30:37.796 --> 30:40.459
AND EVERY TIME
I TRY TO SUCK IT UP AND SHUT UP

30:40.459 --> 30:43.012
AND JUST BE COLD AND NORMAL,
I END UP DRUNK...

30:43.012 --> 30:45.764
OR ON PILLS
OR AT A FUNERAL.

30:50.139 --> 30:52.391
DO YOU KNOW WHAT IT FELT LIKE
TO WALK INTO THAT TRAUMA ROOM

30:52.391 --> 30:54.603
AND SEE YOU ON THAT TABLE
AND THINK TO MYSELF,

30:54.603 --> 30:56.645
"GREAT.
I DID IT AGAIN.

30:56.645 --> 30:58.237
HERE COMES
ANOTHER FUNERAL."

31:00.109 --> 31:04.113
[ SIGHS ]

31:04.113 --> 31:06.615
YOU KNOW WHAT?

31:06.615 --> 31:08.117
FORGET IT.
I...

31:10.289 --> 31:12.751
I DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHY I CAME IN.

31:12.751 --> 31:14.873
[ SIGHS ]

31:24.713 --> 31:27.466
[ SIREN WAILING IN DISTANCE ]

31:34.433 --> 31:36.105
Richard: HELLO.

31:39.438 --> 31:41.110
CROSS...

31:41.110 --> 31:43.692
LET'S GET DR. GREY
A WHEELCHAIR.

31:43.692 --> 31:48.867
♪ I GOT SUNSHINE ♪

31:48.867 --> 31:52.992
♪ ON A CLOUDY DAY ♪

31:52.992 --> 31:57.126
♪ WHEN IT'S COLD OUTSIDE ♪

31:57.126 --> 32:01.210
♪ I GOT
THE MONTH OF MAY ♪

32:01.210 --> 32:07.466
♪ WELL, I GUESS
YOU'D SAY ♪

32:07.466 --> 32:11.640
♪ WHAT CAN MAKE ME
FEEL THIS WAY? ♪

32:17.266 --> 32:20.149
I UNDERSTAND
YOU SAW AMELIA.

32:20.149 --> 32:21.320
LOOK, LOOK, LOOK.

32:21.320 --> 32:23.272
I KNOW YOU'RE NOT
IN THE MOOD FOR A LECTURE.

32:26.445 --> 32:28.327
BUT...

32:28.327 --> 32:30.869
ARE YOU FINISHED?

32:36.835 --> 32:40.539
SHE CAME TO SEE YOU
THE NIGHT AFTER THE ATTACK.

32:40.539 --> 32:43.462
SHE WAS DRUNK.

32:43.462 --> 32:46.345
SHE WAS UPSET...

32:46.345 --> 32:51.680
BECAUSE YOU'D CALLED HER
FOR A CONSULT THAT DAY --

32:51.680 --> 32:54.643
THE DAY OF THE ATTACK.

32:54.643 --> 32:56.015
AND SHE HAD A CHOICE

32:56.015 --> 33:01.020
BETWEEN COMING TO YOU
AND GOING TO ANOTHER TRAUMA,

33:01.020 --> 33:03.902
AND SHE WENT
TO THE OTHER TRAUMA

33:03.902 --> 33:05.604
BECAUSE SHE WAS MAD AT YOU.

33:11.320 --> 33:13.872
FORGIVENESS IS
A POWERFUL THING, MEREDITH...

33:16.455 --> 33:20.619
...NOT ONLY TO MAKE
THE OTHER PERSON FEEL GOOD,

33:20.619 --> 33:23.172
BUT TO HEAL YOU.

33:25.294 --> 33:28.006
YOU NEED TO FORGIVE HER,
MER.

33:29.968 --> 33:32.051
FORGIVE HER
FOR NOT BEING DEREK...

33:33.932 --> 33:36.725
...FOR BEING
THE WRONG SHEPHERD...

33:36.725 --> 33:40.269
JUST ENOUGH TO REMIND YOU
OF WHAT'S MISSING,

33:40.269 --> 33:43.352
BUT NOT ENOUGH
TO BRING HIM BACK.

33:43.352 --> 33:47.066
THAT'S NOT HER FAULT.

33:47.066 --> 33:49.818
YOU NEED TO FORGIVE HER.

33:49.818 --> 33:53.742
YOU DON'T HAVE TO LIKE HER.

33:53.742 --> 33:57.826
YOU DON'T HAVE TO LOVE HER.

33:57.826 --> 34:01.080
BUT FORGIVE HER, OKAY?

34:01.080 --> 34:06.715
SO YOU CAN FORGIVE BLAKE
FOR BEING IN THAT ROOM

34:06.715 --> 34:09.128
WHEN A WRONG DECISION
COST YOU YOUR HUSBAND.

34:09.128 --> 34:11.090
[ SIGHS ]

34:11.090 --> 34:16.265
TO FORGIVE DEREK
FOR DYING TOO SOON.

34:18.557 --> 34:21.100
TO FORGIVE YOURSELF

34:21.100 --> 34:23.982
FOR HATING HIM
FOR DYING TOO SOON.

34:29.738 --> 34:32.691
LET IT GO, MEREDITH...

34:32.691 --> 34:34.493
[ SNIFFLES ]

34:34.493 --> 34:35.864
...AND FORGIVE.

34:39.158 --> 34:42.201
[ SIGHS ]

34:46.125 --> 34:49.338
SUN FEELS GOOD ON THE FACE,
DOESN'T IT?

34:52.171 --> 34:54.012
April: WHAT IS THE POINT
OF COUNSELING, THEN,

34:54.012 --> 34:56.345
IF YOU'RE JUST GONNA SUDDENLY,
WITHOUT EVEN TALKING ABOUT IT,

34:56.345 --> 34:57.476
JUST --
OH, COME ON.

34:57.476 --> 34:59.388
ALL WE DO IS TALK, APRIL.
SO, WHAT?

34:59.388 --> 35:01.520
YOU JUST -- YOU JUST --
JUST SERVE ME PAPERS?

35:01.520 --> 35:04.813
JUST LIKE THAT?
JUST NO WARNING, NO -- NO ANY--

35:04.813 --> 35:07.486
DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA
WHAT A SLAP IN THE FACE THIS IS?

35:10.729 --> 35:12.321
ARE YOU KIDDING ME?

35:14.533 --> 35:16.535
[ SIGHS ]
YOU READY?

35:19.788 --> 35:22.411
♪♪

35:34.343 --> 35:36.094
HI, DR. GREY.

35:36.094 --> 35:37.216
LOU.

35:37.216 --> 35:40.018
UM...

35:40.018 --> 35:41.600
THANK YOU FOR MEETING ME.

35:51.360 --> 35:55.654
THIS IS MY WIFE, JOANNE,

35:55.654 --> 35:57.115
MY DAUGHTER, KYLIE.

35:57.115 --> 36:01.370
I TOLD YOU ABOUT HER --
THE YOUNGEST, REALLY SMART.

36:01.370 --> 36:03.782
AND THAT'S MY ANNE.

36:04.873 --> 36:06.705
UM...

36:06.705 --> 36:08.837
UM, HAVE A SEAT, GIRLS.

36:08.837 --> 36:11.340
UM, YOU GOT KIDS?

36:13.382 --> 36:15.714
RIGHT.

36:15.714 --> 36:16.505
FORGOT YOU CAN'T TALK.

36:16.505 --> 36:20.098
THE...JAW.

36:20.098 --> 36:22.971
UM...

36:22.971 --> 36:25.684
I WANTED TO...

36:29.147 --> 36:32.811
I DIDN'T KNOW
WHAT I WAS DOING.

36:32.811 --> 36:33.902
WHAT I DID TO YOU...

36:36.114 --> 36:38.487
I DIDN'T KNOW.

36:38.487 --> 36:40.739
I WOULD NEVER...

36:40.739 --> 36:44.913
I WOULD NEVER
HURT A WOMAN.

36:47.416 --> 36:49.628
I...

36:49.628 --> 36:51.750
I JUST WANT YOU...

36:51.750 --> 36:54.293
I JUST WANT YOU
TO KNOW THAT I'M SORRY.

36:57.426 --> 37:01.470
TRULY SORRY.

37:01.470 --> 37:04.263
♪♪

37:27.496 --> 37:29.748
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

37:47.596 --> 37:50.389
[ THUNDER CRASHES ]

37:50.389 --> 37:52.691
[ CLINKING ]

37:59.027 --> 38:00.899
IT'S MY 30-DAY CHIP.

38:03.111 --> 38:04.863
I'M SOBER.

38:04.863 --> 38:07.826
AND I'M STARTING BACK AT WORK
ON MONDAY, SO...

38:07.826 --> 38:09.328
I'M TRYING.

38:12.711 --> 38:14.373
I'M TRYING.

38:17.966 --> 38:20.589
Meredith: I KNOW YOU ARE.

38:22.761 --> 38:25.013
YOU...

38:25.013 --> 38:27.346
YOU CAN TALK.
THAT, UM...

38:27.346 --> 38:28.477
THAT'S GREAT.

38:28.477 --> 38:30.769
THEY, UH,
TOOK THE WIRES OFF?

38:30.769 --> 38:32.481
YEAH, THIS MORNING.

38:33.392 --> 38:35.023
[ THUNDER CRASHES ]

38:39.568 --> 38:43.241
I'M JUST NOT READY
TO FORGIVE YOU YET.

38:46.154 --> 38:47.706
I'M NOT...

38:49.908 --> 38:52.160
...EXACTLY READY, EITHER.

38:55.504 --> 38:58.417
SEE YOU LATER.

38:58.417 --> 39:00.839
SEE YOU LATER.

39:05.554 --> 39:07.556
[ THUNDER CRASHES ]

39:11.640 --> 39:14.473
[ ARON WRIGHT'S "I SURRENDER"
PLAYS ]

39:23.942 --> 39:29.538
♪ OH, THIS ROAD HAS BEEN HARD ♪

39:29.538 --> 39:33.912
♪ ON MY FEET, ON MY HEART ♪
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

39:33.912 --> 39:38.126
♪ LED ME TO THE GATES OF HELL ♪

39:38.126 --> 39:42.881
♪ I KNOW SORROW ALL TOO WELL ♪

39:42.881 --> 39:45.464
♪ LOST MY LOVE TO THE WIND ♪

39:45.464 --> 39:47.506
[ SIGHS ]

39:47.506 --> 39:52.641
♪ LEFT ME HALF OF WHO I AM ♪
[ GRUNTING ]

39:52.641 --> 39:54.473
♪ HEAVY LOAD ♪
[ SCREAMING, GLASS SHATTERING ]

39:54.473 --> 39:55.604
[ SIGHS ]

39:55.604 --> 40:01.780
♪ HEAVEN KNOWS, I'M TIRED ♪

40:01.780 --> 40:03.321
♪ I GIVE UP ♪

40:03.321 --> 40:06.074
MER.

40:06.074 --> 40:08.156
♪ I GIVE IN ♪

40:08.156 --> 40:10.659
LET'S GO.

40:10.659 --> 40:15.534
♪ I LAY DOWN ♪

40:15.534 --> 40:18.707
♪ I SURRENDER ♪

40:20.298 --> 40:21.339
♪ I WON'T FIGHT ♪
DO YOU WANT ANYTHING?

40:21.339 --> 40:23.592
YOU KNOW --
LIKE A SANDWICH OR A...

40:23.592 --> 40:25.093
OR A BLANKET?

40:25.093 --> 40:26.805
ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT.
I'M GOOD. I'M GOOD.

40:26.805 --> 40:28.507
SIT DOWN, SIT DOWN.

40:28.507 --> 40:33.431
♪ I LAY DOWN ♪

40:33.431 --> 40:35.554
I JUST SPENT SIX WEEKS IN A BED,
UNABLE TO SPEAK.

40:35.554 --> 40:37.185
♪ AT YOUR SIDE ♪

40:37.185 --> 40:39.397
WHEN THAT HAPPENS,
YOU SEE THINGS.

40:39.397 --> 40:42.270
♪ I SURRENDER ♪
THERE'S A LOT OF THINGS THAT
PEOPLE DON'T SAY TO EACH OTHER

40:42.270 --> 40:43.942
THAT THEY SHOULD JUST SAY,

40:43.942 --> 40:46.525
SO I NEED YOU TO HEAR ME
WHEN I SAY THIS.

40:46.525 --> 40:49.738
♪ AFTER ALL I'VE BEEN THROUGH ♪
I KNOW I'VE NEEDED YOU
A LOT LATELY.

40:49.738 --> 40:52.491
♪ I CAN'T SAY WHAT IS TRUE ♪
BUT I ALSO KNOW, AND
I HAVE KNOWN FOR A LONG TIME

40:52.491 --> 40:53.532
THAT JO LOVES YOU.

40:53.532 --> 40:55.283
♪ BUT I CHOOSE TO BELIEVE ♪

40:55.283 --> 40:57.916
"POST-IT ON THE WALL"
LOVES YOU.

40:57.916 --> 40:59.628
♪ THERE'S A HAND GUIDING ME ♪

40:59.628 --> 41:01.880
DON'T IGNORE THAT.

41:01.880 --> 41:04.082
♪ THERE IS HOPE ♪
YOU CAN HAVE
MORE THAN ONE PERSON.

41:04.082 --> 41:06.344
♪ THERE'S A HOME ♪
I USED TO THINK YOU COULDN'T,
BUT NOW I KNOW.

41:06.344 --> 41:08.426
I MEAN, TURNS OUT
I HAVE A WHOLE DAMN VILLAGE.

41:08.426 --> 41:09.548
[ CHUCKLES ]

41:09.548 --> 41:12.010
SO YOU DON'T HAVE
TO WORRY ABOUT ME.

41:12.010 --> 41:13.722
♪ I GIVE UP ♪
GO BE WITH JO.

41:13.722 --> 41:16.224
I'LL BE FINE.
I'M OKAY.

41:16.224 --> 41:20.769
♪ I GIVE IN ♪

41:20.769 --> 41:25.443
♪ I LAY DOWN ♪

41:25.443 --> 41:29.988
♪ I SURRENDER ♪

41:29.988 --> 41:34.573
♪ I WON'T FIGHT ♪

41:34.573 --> 41:39.578
♪ I WON'T TRY ♪

41:39.578 --> 41:43.922
♪ I LAY DOWN ♪
DON'T LET FEAR KEEP YOU QUIET.

41:43.922 --> 41:47.175
♪ AT YOUR SIDE ♪
"AND THE MOON
GAVE EVERYTHING A MAGICAL GLOW

41:47.175 --> 41:49.588
AS IF THEY WERE DANCING
ON THE MILKY WAY."

41:49.588 --> 41:50.589
♪ I WON'T CRY ♪

41:50.589 --> 41:51.800
MOMMY.
YES?

41:51.800 --> 41:53.842
YOU HAVE A VOICE.

41:53.842 --> 41:57.726
♪ WHY SHOULDN'T I? ♪
SO USE IT.

41:57.726 --> 42:00.769
♪ I LAY DOWN ♪
SPEAK UP.

42:00.769 --> 42:02.140
RAISE YOUR HANDS.

42:02.140 --> 42:03.521
SHOUT YOUR ANSWERS.

42:03.521 --> 42:05.644
♪ AT YOUR SIDE ♪
MAKE YOURSELF HEARD.

42:05.644 --> 42:07.736
WHATEVER IT TAKES.

42:07.736 --> 42:10.739
JUST FIND YOUR VOICE.

42:10.739 --> 42:11.740
AND WHEN YOU DO...

42:11.740 --> 42:15.033
♪ I SURRENDER ♪

42:15.033 --> 42:17.535
...FILL THE DAMN SILENCE.
